  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some of the best ways to buy PC games at a low rate?",
  "response": "There are several ways to buy PC games at a discounted price. Here are some of the best options:\n\n1. **Steam Sales:**\n   - Steam frequently holds seasonal sales (e.g., Summer Sale, Winter Sale) where many games are heavily discounted. You can also find weekly or daily deals on their platform.\n\n2. **Humble Bundle:**\n   - Humble Bundle offers bundles of games at a pay-what-you-want price, often including both older titles and new releases. They also have a Humble Store with regular sales and discounts.\n\n3. **GOG (Good Old Games):**\n   - GOG often has sales similar to Steam, with DRM-free games. They also have a section called \"GOG Connect\" where you can link your Steam account to get some games for free.\n\n4. **Epic Games Store:**\n   - The Epic Games Store frequently offers weekly free games and has sales on popular titles. They also have exclusive games that can sometimes be purchased at a discount.\n\n5. **Green Man Gaming:**\n   - Green Man Gaming offers competitive prices and often has additional discounts with coupon codes. They also have a VIP program for frequent buyers.\n\n6. **Fanatical:**\n   - Fanatical offers bundles and flash sales on a variety of games. They are known for their \"Build a Bundle\" deals where you can choose games from a selection and pay a discounted price.\n\n7. **Key Resellers:**\n   - Websites like Kinguin and G2A sell game keys at a discount. Be cautious, as some keys may be region-locked or from questionable sources. Always check the seller's ratings and reviews.\n\n8. **Subscription Services:**\n   - Services like Xbox Game Pass for PC offer a library of games for a monthly fee, which can be cost-effective if you play a lot of different games.\n\n9. **Retailer Sales:**\n   - Keep an eye on physical and online retailers like Amazon, Best Buy, and Walmart, especially during holiday sales. They often have discounts on game codes and physical copies.\n\n10. **Newsletters and Social Media:**\n    - Many game developers and distributors offer exclusive discounts to newsletter subscribers or social media followers. Following your favorite game companies can lead to special deals.\n\n11. **Wishlists:**\n    - Adding games to your wishlist on platforms like Steam or the Epic Games Store can sometimes result in notifications about price drops or special promotions.\n\nBy keeping an eye on these options and timing your purchases during sales, you can significantly reduce the cost of your PC game library.",
